KMC fails to pay farmers Sh380m             Peterson Githaiga  18th Sep 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 Peterson Githaiga  18th Sep 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 Peterson Githaiga   Angry farmers protest at the gates of the Kenya Meat Commission yesterday in Athi River. The farmers said the meat firm owes them Sh380 million and the payment has been delayed for the last three years. They want the government to intervene. [Peterson Githaiga, Standard]  Angry farmers protest at the gates of the Kenya Meat Commission yesterday in Athi River. The farmers said the meat firm owes them Sh380 million and the payment has been delayed for the last three years. They want the government to intervene. [Peterson Githaiga, Standard] Angry farmers protest at the gates of the Kenya Meat Commission yesterday in Athi River. The farmers said the meat firm owes them Sh380 million and the payment has been delayed for the last three years. They want the government to intervene.       Graft and mismanagement   For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper. For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.      Financial crisis       We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. HERE Related Topics Kenya Meat Commission Athi River Farmers unpaid dues